{"status":"success","result":"Claude CLI's analysis is sharp. I agree with all four points. A few additions from my seat:\n\n*On the fast-path suggestion* — word count alone is risky. \"Fix it\" is 2 words and needs the Coder. Better signal: word count AND no action verbs AND no code markers. Claude CLI's instinct is right but the implementation needs tightening.\n\n*What Claude CLI didn't surface:*\n\n• *Resource contention* — qwen2.5vl:72b does triple duty: Artist, Cinematographer, and vision classifier. If it's mid-video-generation when an image message comes in, what happens? That race condition isn't handled anywhere visible.\n\n• *Prompt versioning* — the classifier prompt lives in code. When it changes (and it will, as you tune it), there's no way to A/B test or roll back without a full deploy. At minimum, externalise it to a file so it can be updated without rebuilding.\n\n• *No test coverage visible for the classifier* — `index.test.ts` exists but I don't know what's in it. The routing logic is now the most critical path in the system and it needs tests.\n\n• *The feedback loop is still just a concept* — both Claude CLI and I have said \"binary feedback could improve the classifier.\" Neither of us has said *how*. That's the actual engineering problem: capture signal → store it → fold it back into the classifier prompt as few-shot examples. That's a feature, not a vague idea.\n\n*The thing I'd push back on Claude CLI about:*\n\nThe `AUTO_ESCALATE_PATTERN` regex for failure detection is still sitting there unchanged. We fixed *upfront* routing with the semantic classifier but *mid-response* failure detection is still regex on apology phrases. That inconsistency will bite eventually.\n\nShould I put together a prioritised backlog based on all of this?","newSessionId":"9ab085a0-060d-41ae-b3d8-a97f4d571171"}
